From [[w:Old English language|Old English]][[category:Old English derivations]] plien, [[w:French language|French]][[category:French derivations]] [[plier]] (meaning ''to [[fold]], to [[bend]]), from [[w:Latin|Latin]][[Category:Latin derivations]] [[plicare]]; akin to [[w:Greek language|Greek]][[Category:Greek derivations]] , [[w:German language|German]][[Category:German derivations]] [[flechten]]. Compare with [[apply]], [[complex]], [[display]], [[duplicity]], [[employ]], [[exploit]], [[implicate]], [[plait]], [[pliant]], [[flax]].

===Noun===
'''ply''' (plural '''plies''')

# A [[layer]] of material. (''two-ply toilet paper'')
# Short for [[plywood]].

===Transitive verb===
'''to ply''' (('''plies''', '''plying''', '''plied''')

# To [[work]] at [[diligent]]ly.  (''ply one's trade'')
# To [[travel]] over [[regular]]ly. (''ply the seven seas'')
# To [[use]] [[vigorous]]ly. (''ply a sword'')

